The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 4: The Life Insurance Corporation of India will soon issue a new policy for non-resident Indians to corner a sizeable slice of the Rs 27,000-crore India Millennium Deposits that comes up for redemption on December 27. Chairman A.K. Shukla said the scheme would be offered to NRIs when they come to India for redeeming the IMDs. Moreover, the overseas branches of LIC will come up with separate schemes depending on the regulations of that country to tap the money from the deposit scheme.

 Mumbai, Nov. 4: India?s foreign exchange reserves rose by $678 million to $143.774 billion during the week ended October 28, the Reserve Bank said in its weekly statistical supplement. Foreign currency assets also increased by $671 million to $137.632 billion.

 Mumbai, Nov. 4: Apollo Hospitals today said it is planning to acquire Andhra-based Samudra Healthcare Enterprises Ltd. The board has constituted a committee to take a final decision on the proposal, Apollo informed the BSE.

 Vienna, Nov. 4: Global crude prices slid today. Light, sweet crude for December delivery fell 49 cents to $61.29 on New York Mercantile Exchange, while December Brent crude futures on London?s Ice Futures Exchange fell 61 cents to $59.91 a barrel.

 Mumbai, Nov. 4: GoAir, the Wadia group promoted budget airline, commenced its commercial operations from today. It hopes to fly 50 million people in the next 3-5 years and add 36 aircraft to its fleet by 2008.




